content.description: Difficult continuous compression problem on arete. Sit Start with left hand a descent side pull and right hand on arete.  Stand up on sloping feet and bump right hand to crimp.  A series of bumps and pinches to the top.
content.location: 35 feet downhill from Mantel of Death.  100 feet north of Don't F with the Bees.  Pretty easy to find.

content.description: Whales on Crack starts on jugs and moves into the large crack then tops out onto the detached block.
content.location: Far right side of Whaler's Rock.

content.description: start with high left side pull and low right hand mantle with a foot smear. Press up and get right foot on and move up. Trust your feet to hold and they might? More fun slabs!
Start on ledge and reach up for a side pull on the bottom of the overhang then get a high foot and reach for the large ledge mantel up onto the ledge then up to the top of the boulder.

Start on the good holds at shoulder height and work your way up the tall arete, avoiding the thin crack out right (Never really comes into play). Cool holds on the arete itself and a few face holds out right lead you to a committing top section.
content.location: On the left side of Whaler’s Rock, immediately right of Bubble Gum Cigar (V0).

content.description: From a stand on compress your way up with awesome moves to an obvious jug about 14 feet up and drop, or continue up to the top.  We topped out, but it is a little sketchy with some big and maybe loose blocks.  Up to the jug is great climbing and still the same grade.   This is a very good climb.
content.location: 5 feet left of Don't F' w/ the bees on the nice wall and arete.

content.description: Start sitting on jug flake down and right.  Climb up using compression encountering a tough move to a sloper near the end.   A good problem.  This was the Harpoon Project.
content.location: JUST past railroad amphitheater take a steep trail up past some cliffs and over other small ones.  Go Straight uphill through the talus field and up into the trees.  Lots of rock around this hidden little spot.  Definitely saw some cool stuff and will be back.  Alternatively Take the balanced rock trail to the top.  Walk 5 or so minutes toward the north shore and 225 paces after the last obvious stairs head down hill into the trees.

content.description: Start on the horizontal break at waist height and work your way up the tall, but easy slab. Be careful for loose rocks.
content.location: On the left side of Whaler’s Rock. In between Trust Face (V3) and Orchestra In Your Head (V4).

content.description: Start down and left in the corridor, bust a mantle, then trend right above the poor landing, encountering a scary delicate crux right at the top that would maybe really suck to botch...  awesome climb.   You can step off if you feel scared.
content.protection: A couple pads, and some good judgement
content.location: 40 feet left of Don't F' w/ the bee's and barely downhill there is a thimble like boulder.  This line faces don't f w/ the bees.  It climbs from the bottom of the corridor and trends right to the top.

content.description: Start in Horizontal crack under rippled roof and work your way up good holds to the top out.
content.location: Just downhill of Don't F with the Bees, on the freestanding boulder.

content.description:
This area is a short cliff line above the Mirror Talus Field, with a few boulders thrown in for good measure.

 Whaler's Rock itself is a large block with multiple lines on it.
